    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae Trinitaris. <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/80">Karlomannus</persName>
                        divina favente gratia <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si loca divino
                        cultui mancipata summopere in omnibus procurare studemus hoc nobis ad
                        presentis vitae prosperitatemn et ad aeternam felicitatem liquido
                        profuturum. Quapropter noverit industria omnium fidelium sanctae Dei
                        Ecclesiae nostrorumque presentium et futurorum, quia venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <persName key="#Baptismal_churches #Abbots" ref="#people/1242"
                            >Theotricus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Penalty #Abbots #Monasteries #Imperial/royal_diploma #Baptismal_churches #Camera_of_other_public_authorities"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/47">beati confessoris Christi
                            Silvestri</orgName> quod <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/15"
                            >Nonantula</placeName> nuncupatur detulit obtutibus nostri <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">preceptum</rs>, in quo continebatur inter
                        cetera, qualiter divae memoriae <persName
                            key="#Baptismal_churches #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/110"
                            >Hludovvici</persName> imperator confirmasset <rs
                            key="#Baptismal_churches">plebem</rs> in loco qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Baptismal_churches" ref="#places/140"><orgName
                                key="#Baptismal_churches #Priests" ref="#juridical_persons/89"
                                >Liziano</orgName></placeName> ad partem ipsius monasterii, de qua
                        contentio fuerat ad partem <placeName key="#Mother_churches #Bishops" ref="#places/7"
                            >Bononiensis</placeName>
                        <orgName key="#Bishops #Mother_churches #Baptismal_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/80"><rs
                                key="#Mother_churches">Ecclesiae</rs></orgName>, et petiit nostram
                        celsitudinem, ut nos eam nostro iterum corrobararemus edictio. Cuius
                        petitionibus pro amore et reverentia ipsius monasterii vel fratrum
                        confirmamus et corroboramus tam preceptum regum seu imperatorum quam vel
                        ipsam plebem sitam in loco qui dicitur Liziano ad partem monasterii
                        Nonantulae, ita videlicet ut <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> Bononiensis
                        ecclesiae ibi consecrationem confirmationem predicationem et <rs
                            key="#Priests">presbiterum</rs>, quem abbas idoneum ad hoc elegerit,
                        inquirat et corrigat. Tempore autem, quo episcopus illuc venire debuerit,
                        abbati innotescat, quatinus ipse sciens ea quae competunt utilitati episcopi
                        necessaria subministret, nec sacerdos pro qualibet occasione videatur
                        opprimi. Amplius vero nullam ibi habet dominationem facere aut quippiam
                        tollere. Igitur ut nostra iussio sit firma, poenam statuimus, ut, si quis
                        contra hoc nostrum preceptum agere temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">XXX
                            libras argenti</rs>
                        <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">eidem monasterio se
                            compositurum sciat</rs>. Et ut haec nostra auctoritas nostrae
                        confirmationis ac concessionis firmior in aevum habebatur, manu propria
                        nostra subtus eam firmavimus et anulo nostro sigillari iussimus. Signum MF
                        Karlomanni piissimi regis. <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Madaluuinus"
                                >Madalvvinus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> ad vicem <persName><name ref="Teudemarius"
                                >Theotmari</name></persName> recognovi et SR NT SID Data III idus
                        augusti, anno III regni Karlomanni serenissimi regis in Bavvaria et in
                        Italia II, indictione XII. Actum in Bavvaria ad <placeName ref="#places/114"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential"
                            >Otinga</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> regia; in Dei nomine amen. </ab>
